Thinking about Otto Skorzeny wearing his SS uniform to socialite parties in Spain after the war and his escape. Everyone in fashionable clothes, suits, etc. and one autist in black paramilitary uniform flexing his medals and expensive watches, enjoying the respect and admiration.

Same type as Auguste Rodin and Orson Welles, larger than life men who loved the attention of others. Orson Welles had an IQ of 185 apparently, had two-three rare steaks with scotch almost every night. Skorzeny even brags in interviews how many countries tried to hire him post-war

I remember when I discovered fellatio (as a pathology we should only refer to it in cold, Faucian terms) I thought it had to be one of those things that people are only memed into pretending to enjoy, seemed like a waste of time.

There is a Skorzeny interview where he jokes about how first Castro wanted to hire him and later Castro's enemies approached him. He smiles and says: "Everyone wants me." Celebrity is bad in the spying and intelligence business, but it's obvious he preferred it to be this way.

Julius Evola admits, if he had been in St. Aquinas' shoes, when a "beautiful whore" was brought to his room to tempt him away from priesthood, he would have simply indulged in the lust of her flesh instead of fighting. Guess this is why there is no "St." in front of Evola's name.

When he had his dream about being enthroned as pope, Evola picked the name "Pope Hermes" (because apparently it had to be something different from your birth name), so I guess that would have been it in the parallel timeline

Evola tells the tale of an enigmatic grave in Germany, belonging to a boy named Kaspar Hauser, who one day emerged from the woods, unable to talk, afraid of fire and mirrors, and able to see in the dark like a cat. Once the people taught him to talk, he said he remembered only...

All our youth are as Kaspar's tragedy today, Evola smiles. If Kaspar had been able to recover the secret of his ancestry (which Melville plaves in the grave), his memory and inheritance, he would have been King. He had to retake his birthright. If one remembers, one seizes power.
